    "body": "## Summary\r\n- Fix accuracy drop (MMLU 75% → 55%) when `multi_stream_moe` and `mlir_elementwise_fusion` are both enabled\r\n- Add `caller_stream.synchronize()` in `begin_aux_stream_passthrough` to fix event-based sync failure with MLIR Triton kernels\r\n- Reclassify piecewise static partitions containing multi-stream ops as dynamic (eager) so the synchronize fix applies during cudagraph replay\r\n- Enable `multi_stream_moe` in the Gemma4 MoE config\r\n\r\n## Details\r\nEvent-based CUDA stream synchronization (`event.record()` + `stream.wait_event()`) is insufficient when MLIR-generated Triton kernels precede the stream switch point. The aux stream can start reading caller-stream tensors before GPU writes have retired, causing illegal memory accesses (with `torch-simple`) or silent data corruption (with `torch-cudagraph`).\r\n\r\nFor piecewise cudagraphs, the host-side `synchronize()` cannot be called during CUDA graph capture. The fix reclassifies static partitions that contain stream-switch passthrough functions as dynamic, so they run eagerly (with the synchronize fix) while single-stream partitions remain captured as CUDA graphs.\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n- [x] `TRTLLM_ACCURACY_NO_REFERENCE=1 pytest tests/integration/defs/accuracy/test_llm_api_autodeploy.py::TestGemma4MoE::test_bf16` — MMLU 75.4%, GSM8K 90.5% (matches baseline)\r\n- [x] Verify no regression on other models using `multi_stream_moe` (GLM-4.7-flash, Qwen3.5 MoE, Nemotron Super)\r\n\r\n\r\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n\r\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\r\n\r\n* **New Features**\r\n  * Added multi-stream mixture-of-experts (MOE) model compilation support.\r\n\r\n* **Bug Fixes**\r\n  * Improved stream synchronization behavior for CUDA graph capture scenarios.\r\n  * Enhanced detection of dynamic operations during graph compilation to improve optimization accuracy.\r\n\r\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
